": \\\"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\\\"}, \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-06-29T17:48:07.534602+00:00\\\"}\\n{\\\"hook_type\\\": \\\"PreToolUse\\\", \\\"payload\\\": {\\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/home/kurtk/codex-hooks-example\\\", \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"PreToolUse\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"permission_mode\\\": \\\"default\\\", \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5\\\", \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"command\\\": \\\"tail -n 80 hooks.log\\\"}, \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Bash\\\", \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"call_xXVinC7Ja2W3OZ3Cm0btSpjT\\\", \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/home/kurtk/.codex/sessions/2026/06/29/rollout-2026-06-29T13-47-18-019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5.jsonl\\\", \\\"turn_id\\\": \\\"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\\\"}, \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-06-29T17:48:07.547630+00:00\\\"}\\n{\\\"hook_type\\\": \\\"PreToolUse\\\", \\\"payload\\\": {\\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/home/kurtk/codex-hooks-example\\\", \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"PreToolUse\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"permission_mode\\\": \\\"default\\\", \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5\\\", \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"command\\\": \\\"sed -n '1,220p' README.md\\\"}, \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Bash\\\", \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"call_5D1slIHeFE8ye508tCEqpicC\\\", \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/home/kurtk/.codex/sessions/2026/06/29/rollout-2026-06-29T13-47-18-019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5.jsonl\\\", \\\"turn_id\\\": \\\"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\\\"}, \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-06-29T17:48:07.554174+00:00\\\"}\\n\", \"tool_use_id\": \"call_xXVinC7Ja2W3OZ3Cm0btSpjT\", \"transcript_path\": \"/home/kurtk/.codex/sessions/2026/06/29/rollout-2026-06-29T13-47-18-019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5.jsonl\", \"turn_id\": \"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\"}, \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-29T17:48:07.656891+00:00\"}\n{\"hook_type\": \"PostToolUse\", \"payload\": {\"cwd\": \"/home/kurtk/codex-hooks-example\", \"hook_event_name\": \"PostToolUse\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"permission_mode\": \"default\", \"session_id\": \"019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5\", \"tool_input\": {\"command\": \"sed -n '1,220p' README.md\"}, \"tool_name\": \"Bash\", \"tool_response\": \"# Codex Hooks Example\\n\\nThis repository contains a project-local Codex hooks setup that logs every\\nsupported hook type to `hooks.log`.\\n\\n## Files\\n\\n- `.codex/hooks.json` configures all supported Codex hook events.\\n- `.codex/hooks/log_hook.py` receives each hook payload on stdin and appends a\\n  JSON line to `hooks.log`.\\n- `hooks.log` is created at the repository root when a hook runs.\\n\\nEach log entry includes:\\n\\n- `timestamp`\\n- `hook_type`\\n- `payload`\\n\\n## Install\\n\\n1. Copy or keep the `.codex/` directory at the root of the repository where you\\n   want these hooks to run.\\n\\n2. Start Codex from inside that repository.\\n\\n3. Make sure the project is trusted. Project-local hooks are loaded only when\\n   the project `.codex/` layer is trusted.\\n\\n4. In the Codex CLI, run:\\n\\n   ```text\\n   /hooks\\n   ```\\n\\n5. Review and trust the hook definitions. Codex records trust for the exact hook\\n   configuration, so changing `.codex/hooks.json` or the command definitions may\\n   require reviewing them again.\\n\\nAfter that, matching hook invocations append JSONL records to `hooks.log`.\\n\\nFor one-off automation that already vets the hook source outside Codex, you can\\nlaunch Codex with:\\n\\n```shell\\ncodex --dangerously-bypass-hook-trust\\n```\\n\\nUse that flag only when you intentionally want to skip persisted hook trust for\\nthat run.\\n\\n## Supported Hook Types\\n\\nThis example configures:\\n\\n- `SessionStart`\\n- `PreToolUse`\\n- `PermissionRequest`\\n- `PostToolUse`\\n- `PreCompact`\\n- `PostCompact`\\n- `UserPromptSubmit`\\n- `SubagentStart`\\n- `SubagentStop`\\n- `Stop`\\n\", \"tool_use_id\": \"call_5D1slIHeFE8ye508tCEqpicC\", \"transcript_path\": \"/home/kurtk/.codex/sessions/2026/06/29/rollout-2026-06-29T13-47-18-019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5.jsonl\", \"turn_id\": \"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\"}, \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-29T17:48:07.656444+00:00\"}\n{\"hook_type\": \"PreToolUse\", \"payload\": {\"cwd\": \"/home/kurtk/codex-hooks-example\", \"hook_event_name\": \"PreToolUse\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"permission_mode\": \"default\", \"session_id\": \"019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5\", \"tool_input\": {\"agent_type\": \"explorer\", \"fork_context\": false, \"message\": \"This is a hook-test task. Do not edit files. Please reply with a one-line message saying the subagent hook trigger test ran, then stop.\"}, \"tool_name\": \"spawn_agent\", \"tool_use_id\": \"call_U9k19fYFGOKZhjAMEqijTc1F\", \"transcript_path\": \"/home/kurtk/.codex/sessions/2026/06/29/rollout-2026-06-29T13-47-18-019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5.jsonl\", \"turn_id\": \"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\"}, \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-29T17:48:20.722728+00:00\"}\n{\"hook_type\": \"PostToolUse\", \"payload\": {\"cwd\": \"/home/kurtk/codex-hooks-example\", \"hook_event_name\": \"PostToolUse\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"permission_mode\": \"default\", \"session_id\": \"019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5\", \"tool_input\": {\"agent_type\": \"explorer\", \"fork_context\": false, \"message\": \"This is a hook-test task. Do not edit files. Please reply with a one-line message saying the subagent hook trigger test ran, then stop.\"}, \"tool_name\": \"spawn_agent\", \"tool_response\": \"{\\\"agent_id\\\":\\\"019f147f-157a-7bc1-9bd2-1b19b004d1af\\\",\\\"nickname\\\":\\\"Planck\\\"}\", \"tool_use_id\": \"call_U9k19fYFGOKZhjAMEqijTc1F\", \"transcript_path\": \"/home/kurtk/.codex/sessions/2026/06/29/rollout-2026-06-29T13-47-18-019f147e-2282-7740-99c9-3eb8d3605be5.jsonl\", \"turn_id\": \"019f147e-b38b-7f60-ba6d-3bcbfd44070c\"}, \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-29T17:48:20.824263+00:00\"}\n{\"hook_type\": \"SubagentStart\", \"payload\": {\"agent_id\": \"019f147f-157a-7b